DOM:
--its a programming interface in web development that allows us to interact and manipulate(change) the html documents.
When the webpage is loaded , the browser creates the dom of that particular web page.

When an html file is loaded into the browser , the javascript cannot understand the html document directly.

DOM is basically the Representation of same html document but in a tree like structure.

HTML DOM: allows javascript  to access (to get and as well as to modify all the elements in the html document). 

Keypoints:
1)Structure:
the dom represents the structure of html document as tree, node in a tree represents the element an attribute, text
2)Management:
using is you caninteract with elements(buttons, h,p), we can modify ,add, ,remove, elements .

Change styles:
3)event handling:
4)world wide web consortium:
